## References

In the not “all hill-climbing” example, the first 10 moves (the 0th-10th moves), where there are substantial variations in Dropdown move distances across the sequences, would be coded as non-hillclimbing (N), while the 10th-20th moves and the 20th-30th moves, where Dropdown move distances are consistently low, would be coded as hillclimbing (H). In the “all hill-climbing” example, all first 30 moves would be coded as hillclimbing (H).
